The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Lever net profit rises
                                                                                                               Lever net profit rises
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, Feb. 13: Hindustan Unilever, the FMCG major, today announced a consolidated net profit of Rs 1,914.88 crore for the financial year ended December 31, 2007 against Rs 1,890.53 crore in the previous year.        
	Consolidated total income during the reporting period stood at Rs 14,366.54 crore against Rs 12,803.90 crore in corresponding period of the previous year.        
	The results for the period were not comparable with last years numbers as the company had amalgamated Modern Foods (India) Ltd and its subsidiary with itself, Hindustan Unilever informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.        
	On a standalone basis, the net profit stood at Rs 1,925.47 crore for the financial year ended December 31, 2007 against Rs 1,855.37 crore in the year-ago period.         
	Income was Rs 3,847.10 crore against Rs 3,263.05 crore in the previous year.                                                                                                                                        
